{"lemma":"سَلَفُ","slug":"سَلَفُ","root":"س.ل.ف","root_slug":"س-ل-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَلَف","root":"سلف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20467","n20474","n20475","n20476","n20477","n20479","n20478"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be over, to be past"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to come before, to precede, to antecede"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lend, to loan, to advance (money)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ancestor(s), forefather(s), forebear(s)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"predecessor(s), forerunner(s)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"One of the earliest Muslims, including Muhammad's companions and followers."},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"brother-in-law"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20467","headword_ar":"سَلَفَ","root":"slf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"text","text":", and accord. to IKtt,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafN","text_ar":"سَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safN","text_ar":"سَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suluwfN","text_ar":"سُلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [both app. correct,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, K) [and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed; passed away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to an end,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to nought;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became cut off:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and, (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salofN","text_ar":"سَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, MF, and so in copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safN","text_ar":"سَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the CK,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suluwfN","text_ar":"سُلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, K) [and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went before,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preceded;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAlf","text_ar":"سالف","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a camel. (K.) In a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salofa radaAdN","text_ar":"سَلْفَ رَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used by poetic"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1408},{"kind":"text","text":"license for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafa","text_ar":"سَلَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this kind of contraction is allowed by the Basrees only in verbs of which the medial radical letter is with kesr or damm, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealoma","text_ar":"عَلْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealima","text_ar":"عَلِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karoma","text_ar":"كَرْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karuma","text_ar":"كَرُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saruEa","text_ar":"سَرُعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafa lahu EamalN SaAliHN","text_ar":"سَلَفَ لَهُ عَمَلٌ صَالِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous, deed of his preceded"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to prepare for him a future reward"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafati Aln~aAqapu","text_ar":"سَلَفَتِ النَّاقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suluwfN","text_ar":"سُلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camel was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, among the foremost of the camels in arriving at the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  [Golius and Freytag mention also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafa","text_ar":"سَلَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a trans. verb; the former explaining it as signifying “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Præteriit, præcessit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"rem; ” and the latter adding “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tempore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"” and assigning to it the inf. ns."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salofN","text_ar":"سَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suluwfN","text_ar":"سُلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as on the authority of the K; in which I find no indication of such a usage of this verb.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafa AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"سَلَفَ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K;) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salofN","text_ar":"سَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AslfhA","text_ar":"اسلفها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned over the land for sowing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or (so in the K, but in the M “ and ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it even with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misolafap","text_ar":"مِسْلَفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, M, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafa AlmazaAdapa","text_ar":"سَلَفَ المَزَادَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salofN","text_ar":"سَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in some copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaf","text_ar":"سَلَف"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He oiled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greased, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzAdp","text_ar":"مزادة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n20474","headword_ar":"سَلْفٌ","root":"slf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bag for travelling-provisions &c., such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiraAb","text_ar":"جِرَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any sort:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiraAb","text_ar":"جِرَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) [and the contr., i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Freytag, from the Kitáb el-Addád:)] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hide not well,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not thoroughly, tanned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asolufN","text_ar":"اَسْلُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suluwfN","text_ar":"سُلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n20475","headword_ar":"سُلْفٌ","root":"slf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[perhaps a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulafN","text_ar":"سُلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain species of bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"not particularized. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misolafN","text_ar":"مِسْلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20476","headword_ar":"سِلْفٌ","root":"slf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and their duals: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salifN","text_ar":"سَلِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places:       -A2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafN","text_ar":"سَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20477","headword_ar":"سَلَفٌ","root":"slf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as have gone before,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preceded;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb; *) [i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preceding generations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliyfN","text_ar":"سَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulofapN","text_ar":"سُلْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saluwfN","text_ar":"سَلُوفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; all quasipl. ns.; (M;) of which the sing. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAlifN","text_ar":"سَالِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Msb: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as have gone before,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preceded, of"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ancestors"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are above"},{"kind":"text","text":"him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in age and in excellence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but this addition is not always agreeable with usage;] one of whom is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAlifN","text_ar":"سَالِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafN","text_ar":"سَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asolaAfN","text_ar":"اَسْلَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sul~aAfN","text_ar":"سُلَّافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [the former a pl. of pauc. and the latter of mult.,] or the latter is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAlifN","text_ar":"سَالِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafN","text_ar":"سَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[said to be, though this is more properly termed, as it is in the M, a quasi-pl. n.]: (IB, Msb, TA:) and, accord. to Zj,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulufN","text_ar":"سُلُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliyfN","text_ar":"سَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulafN","text_ar":"سُلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulofapN","text_ar":"سُلْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobapN","text_ar":"عُصْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has passed away:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAlifN","text_ar":"سَالِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliyfN","text_ar":"سَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going before; preceding;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaqad~imN","text_ar":"مُتَقَدِّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) [Accord. to Abu-lMahásin,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alafu","text_ar":"السَّلَفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is particularly applied to 'Áïsheh the wife of Mohammad, the three Khaleefehs Aboo-Bekr and 'Omar and 'Othmán, Talhah and Ez-Zubeyr, the Khaleefeh Mo'áwiyeh, and 'Amr Ibn-El-Ás. (De Sacy's Chrest. Ar., sec. ed., i. 156.)] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alafu AlS~aAliHu","text_ar":"السَّلَفُ الصَّالِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the first chief persons of the Tábi'ees. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alafu Almuqad~amu","text_ar":"السَّلَفُ المُقَدَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of the prophet Mohammad. (Ham p. 780.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*aAhibu","text_ar":"مَذَاهِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alafi","text_ar":"السَّلَفِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tenets of the early Muslims."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, going before,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preceding, in journeying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men; as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='aniY salafN mina Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَنِى سَلَفٌ مِنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company of men came to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous, deed, that one has done beforehand"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by way of preparing a future reward"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraT","text_ar":"فَرَط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cause of reward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense, in the world to come, such as a child dying in infancy"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as it were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goes before one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, O, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salamN","text_ar":"سَلَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, Hr, Mgh, O, K, TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any money,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property, paid in advance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beforehand, as the price of a commodity for which the seller has become responsible and which one has bought on description:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"payment for a commodity to be delivered at a certain"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"future"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period with something additional to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the equivalent of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the current price at the time of such payment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"this [transaction] being a cause of profit to him who makes such payment; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salamN","text_ar":"سَلَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also has this meaning: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of sale in which the price is paid in advance, and the commodity is withheld, on the condition of description, to a certain"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"future"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) it is a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isolaAfu","text_ar":"الاـِسْلَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, * K, TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A loan"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroDN","text_ar":"قَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no profit"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Hr, O, Mgh, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the lender"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Hr, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except recompense"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the world to come"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and thanks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which it is incumbent on the recipient thereof to return as he received it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Hr, O, K, TA:) thus the Arabs term it: (Hr, O, TA:) and in this sense also the word is a subst."},{"kind":"page_break","n":1409},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isolaAfu","text_ar":"الاـِسْلَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stallion-camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M, TA.)       -A3-  Also, (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulofapN","text_ar":"سُلْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepuce of a boy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, TA;) so says Lth; (O, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salifN","text_ar":"سَلِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silofN","text_ar":"سِلْفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same; for this is meant by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljilodu","text_ar":"الجِلْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alifu","text_ar":"السَّلِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ilofu","text_ar":"السِّلْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K, in some copies of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxulodu","text_ar":"الخُلْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljilodu","text_ar":"الجِلْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","IB","Msb","M","T","O","Hr","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n20479","headword_ar":"سَلَفٌ","root":"slf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hajal","text_ar":"حَجَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"partridge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, K:) or, accord. to Kr,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAp","text_ar":"قَطَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTFA","text_ar":"قَطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: (M:) AA says that he had not heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulafapN","text_ar":"سُلَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to the female; but if one said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulafapN","text_ar":"سُلَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulakapN","text_ar":"سُلَكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning a single female of what are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silokaAni","text_ar":"سِلْكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it would be approvable: (S:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silofaAni","text_ar":"سِلْفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulofaAnN","text_ar":"سُلْفَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silofaAnN","text_ar":"سِلْفَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"not particularized. (M.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulaHN","text_ar":"سُلَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulakN","text_ar":"سُلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20478","headword_ar":"سَلِفٌ","root":"slf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silofN","text_ar":"سِلْفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband of the sister of the wife"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man: (S, K:) and [the duals]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salifaAni","text_ar":"سَلِفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silofaAni","text_ar":"سِلْفَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two husbands of two sisters:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) accord. to IAar, the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salifapN","text_ar":"سَلِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silofapN","text_ar":"سِلْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is not applied to a woman; (M;) one only uses the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salifaAni","text_ar":"سَلِفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to two men: (M:) or, (M, K,) accord. to Kr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salifataAni","text_ar":"سَلِفَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silofataAni","text_ar":"سِلْفَتَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two wives of two brothers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) [in the present day, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silofapN","text_ar":"سِلْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning a woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband's sister,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and her"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brother's wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. applied to men is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asolaAfN","text_ar":"اَسْلَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, TA,) and that applied to women is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafN","text_ar":"سَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAy^ifu","text_ar":"سَلَايِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence."}],"source_refs":["S","K","M","TA"]}]}}